Package: DICEPRO
Title: Deconvolution with Iterative Completion for Estimating Cellular Proportions from RNA-seq Data
Version: 0.0.1.9
Authors@R: c(
    person("Kalidou", "BA",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "kalidou.ba@u-bordeaux.fr"),
    person("Boris P.", "Hejblum",
           role  = "aut",
           email = "boris.hejblum@u-bordeaux.fr"))
Description: Performs semi-supervised deconvolution of bulk RNA-seq data.
    Known cell-type proportions are estimated via a supervised step
    (CIBERSORTx, FARDEEP, DCQ, CDSeq, or BayesPrism) while unknown
    populations are discovered and quantified through Non-Negative Matrix
    Factorisation (NMF) with L-BFGS-B optimisation. Hyperparameters are
    selected automatically via Pareto-frontier and knee-point detection,
    making the method applicable even when the reference signature matrix
    is incomplete.
